HEADWORD: Palilogy
<hw>Pa*lil"o*gy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>palilogia</ets>, Gr. <grk>palillogi`a</grk>; <grk>pa`lin</grk>
again + <grk>le`gein</grk> to speak.]</ety> <fld>(Rhet.)</fld> <def>The
repetition of a word, or part of a sentence, for the sake of greater
emphasis; <as>as, ⟦ldquo⟧The <ex>living</ex>, the <ex>living</ex>, he
shall praise thee</as>.⟦rdquo⟧</def> <rj><au>Is. xxxviii.
19.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

